title: Killing Venenatis

properties.name: description
properties.value: The profit rate assumes you are soloing Venenatis with range and averaging 8 kills per hour. Your actual profits may be higher or lower depending on your speed and luck.

content:
The methods in this guide may involve considerable risk, including (but not limited to): loss of money/items, unstable prices, and/or slow GE resale.
Reason: Venenatis is located in the Wilderness, do not bring items you are not willing to lose
Killing Venenatis
Requirements
Skills
80+
74+ recommended for Rigour
Items
  • Weapons: Armadyl Crossbow
  • Armour: Ranged equipment: Black d'hide,
  • Food & Potions: Monkfish or better, Divine ranging potions, Prayer potions, Antidote++
  • See Venenatis/Strategies for further detailed equipment
Quest
None
Other
If you can get a spider slayer task from the wilderness slayer master Krystilia, wear the slayer helmet.

The profit rate assumes you are soloing Venenatis with range and averaging 8 kills per hour. Your actual profits may be higher or lower depending on your speed and luck.

Venenatis' most valuable drops are the Venenatis spiderling, Treasonous ring, and the Dragon pickaxe.

Strategy

See the Venenatis article and the strategy guide for additional information.

Due to constantly changing prices on the Grand Exchange, some information in this article may or may not be current.
It is strongly recommended to check the live prices on the Grand Exchange before making large investments in any method.
